Hitech Engineering Co said it agreedto make a new version of (Electrohome Ltd's) large-screen videoprojector and to obtain certification for the projector on theDefense Department's preferred products list.    Under the agreement, Kitchener, Ontario-based Electrohomewill pay an undisclosed amount to Hitech for initial researchand development and to buy some of the units, the Tempestversion of the ECP2000.    The Tempest program is a classified U.S. Government programdealing with data processing equipment. Reuter&#3;